PATIENTFHIR returns the fields of a single Patient as a pipe-delimited row so the frontend can assemble a FHIR-compliant JSON object client-side. Params: PARAM.user_id (caller's sub — gates access) and PARAM.id (patient resource id). Output field order: id, name_use, family, given, gender, birthDate, telecom_system, telecom_value, telecom_use, addr_use, addr_type, addr_line, addr_city, addr_state, addr_postalCode, addr_country. If the patient is not owned by the caller, emits "ERROR|not_found_or_not_authorized" instead. Showcase for FHIR round-trip: ingested via /import as denormalized fields, emitted via this program in the same flat shape for client reassembly into the FHIR nested structure.
